The ANZSoilML GlobalSoilMap application schema is an application of GML/Observations and Measurements that has been developed by members of the Oceania node of the GlobalSoilMap.net project (http://globalsoilmap.net/). It uses the ANZSoilML extensions of O&M to create GML feature types that provide meta-data about: - GSM spatial entities as a special type of ANZSoilML SoilProfile (an O&M SF_SpatialSamplingFeature) - The depth intervals as a special type of ANZSoilML SoilLayer (an O&M SF_SpatialSamplingFeature) - The predicted values as an om:OM_Measure.
This application schema conforms to version 2.3 of the GlobalSoilMap.net Specifications (http://globalsoilmap.net/specifications).

New feature type to satisfy the need for a feature of interest in O&M and overcoming the fact that the GSM specifies the properties that are to be measured, and where those measurements will apply (the SpatialEntity), but not what the properties are of.
A GSM_Process is a placeholder class that provides an instance of an OM_Process that can be used to briefly describe (using gml:description) the process used to make a soil property prediction.

The GSM_SecondarySpatialEntity is defined as a volume of soil to a depth of 2 m (or bedrock if bedrock occurs within less than 2 m) for a rectangular area with regular, fixed horizontal dimensions of 100 m by 100 m located at the centre of a defined global grid of 3 arc-seconds by 3 arc-seconds (approximately 93 m x 93 m at the equator).

A GSM_PrimarySpatialEntity provides point spatial support. It is operationally defined as a volume of soil to a depth of 2 m (or bedrock if bedrock occurs within less than 2 m) for a rectangular area with small and irregular horizontal dimensions of less than 2 m by 2 m (effectively a pedon at point support) located at the centre of a defined global grid of 3 arc-seconds by 3 arc-seconds (approximately 93 m x 93 m at the equator). The point estimate of the GSM_PrimarySpatialEntity may be necessary to produce estimates for the GSM_SecondarySpatialEntity.

Constraints To be documented in conformance classes. 1. A GSM_SpatialEntity shall have an associated parameter with the name 'non soil' and a value of 0 or 1.1 2.1 If the 'non soil' parameter value is 0 then a GSM_SpatialEntity shall have two related om:OM_Observations (list observed properties - new constraint?) and six related anzsmls;SoilLayers. Each anzsmls;SoilLayer shall have ten related om:OM_Observations (list observed properties - new constraint?). 2.2 If the 'non soil' parameter value is 1 then a GSM_SpatialEntity shall have one nil-ed (inapplicable) related om:OM_Observations one nil-ed (inapplicable) related. Their absence should be reinforced with a nil xlink:href denoting nil:inapplicable.2 3. The sampledFeature for a GSM_SpatialEntity shall be an anzsmls:Soil. 4. om:OM_Observations shall be of type OM_Measurement. 5.1 The result of an om:OM_Observation shall be of type gml:Measure. Is this explicit in 4? 5.2 The result quality value shall be an UncertML DQ_UncertaintyResult.3 6. The procedure for an om:OM_Observation shall be a reference to a controlled concept description the pedo-transfer function used to generate the value. 7. All unit of measure values shall be references to the UCUM scheme.4 8. The handling of nil values shall conform to GML-nil.5 Notes 1 See GSM Specification 1.5 'Excluded Non-soil Areas' 2 Depending on final status of GML-nil. 3 See https://wiki.aston.ac.uk/foswiki/bin/view/UncertWeb/OandMProfiles. Need to discuss variation from the profile. 4 perhaps have a observedProperty/UoM constraint explicitly mapping one t'other. 5 Discuss state of GML-nil.
NOTE: certain types omitted for clarity (eg SamplingFeatureComplex). Only a sub-set of Observations/observedProperties are shown.
